            "role": "freelancer",
            "status": "active",
            "time_submitted": 1536910137,
            "description": "One bad review should count as maybe 50. People are reluctant to give bad reviews, but that doesn't help the community. A positive review...easy peasy. I hired Narola largely based on the rating/reviews. \n\nI made it clear from the beginning that communication needed to be clear and constant. I also described my level (beg-int) and that I would be relying on them for answers to help evolve the application. \n\nFrom day 1, communication was weak. I would ask repeatedly to address the issue in question, and it would go unanswered. Eventually, I was connected with one of the actual programmers. It was an improvement, but not much. \n\nGoing back to relying on them. I don't think they are actually technically strong. They didn't know how to answer queries or tackle the tasks in front of them. It wouldn't have been a surprise to them, as I was very clear about this upfront. \n\nThe largest disappointment was the results vs cost. Even though the hourly rate is compelling, the hours definitely racked up. And with little production. High cost, little value. \n\nBe wary. I am now working with onlinejobs.ph and the experience is night and day better.",
