            "role": "freelancer",
            "status": "active",
            "time_submitted": 1501523174,
            "description": "Well done work\n\n[07 March, 2017] Very enthusiastic team and professional. I marked communication lower because of the time difference between US and India. It does make project coordination a challenges. Also, there were a couple of issues where communication was a problem and it delayed the project. Overall I feel it is an excellent value for what it paid.\n\n[08 March, 2017] Excellent progress, a long way to go but I am confident in the team!\n\n[08 March, 2017] Well done so far\n\n[08 March, 2017] Pleasure to work with!\n\n[08 March, 2017] Things are progressing well.\n\n[08 March, 2017] Really enjoy working with this team!\n\n[08 March, 2017] Hope to continue this business relationship for some time to come! Great group of people!\n\n[08 March, 2017] Smart and well rounded team!\n\n[08 March, 2017] I highly recommend this company for virtually any project!\n\n[08 March, 2017] Web applications, mobile applications, database design - they have it all covered. I am very pleased with the progress!\n\n[08 March, 2017] Excellent job so far.\n\n[08 March, 2017] Very creative team, smart and thoughtful. They really try to understand the project and deliver a high quality project.\n\n[08 March, 2017] Very please with the work.\n\n[08 March, 2017] My project is pretty complicated. WIth back end big data, user interface, mobile application, etc. but this team it capable of it all. I am very lucky to have selected them!\n\n[16 March, 2017] This team continues to perform exceptionally. Addressing issues quickly, asking the right questions and responding promptly.\n\n[24 March, 2017] Great team.\n\n[24 March, 2017] The team continues to progress well.\n\n[05 April, 2017] The project is progressing well. The team continues to focus and works well for me.\n\n[05 April, 2017] Great team to work with. Very patient and very accommodating!\n\n[22 April, 2017] Communication remains challenge, primarily in understanding the requirements. Quality continues to lack in that they want to move onto another segment of the app before completely locking in what is being worked on. Here again, I think language, time zone and industry experience continue to play a role in the communication and quality. I can't exactly hold this against anyone, but it does prove challenging.\n\n[22 April, 2017] We continue to push forward. They try very hard to do the right thing. I would recommend to anyone who engages them to be prepared to engage on a full time basis. Being one of many projects can be difficult in picking up one week where we left off the prior week. It is an element of contacting, and is compounded by the time difference, language and general experience in industry/business all in all, they are a great group of people really trying to do their very best. That is what matters.\n\n[27 April, 2017] This is very sensitive to meeting the client expectations. They are open to both positive and negative feedback and address client concerns immediately. Quite impressive to be honest. I definitely recommend this team for any level of project.\n\n[03 July, 2017] Great work\n\n[03 July, 2017] Great team to work with\n\n[03 July, 2017] Looking forward to continuing the project. Great work!\n\n[03 July, 2017] Highly recommend them! Keep up the great work.\n\n[03 July, 2017] Great team to work with\n\n[03 July, 2017] Professionals all the way\n\n[03 July, 2017] Flexible and talented to say the least\n\n[03 July, 2017] Pleasure to work with\n\n[03 July, 2017] Look forward to doing more work with them.\n\n[31 July, 2017] Great work, as always\n\n[31 July, 2017] Continue to perform well\n\n[31 July, 2017] Continue to rely on this team for all development efforts. Well done.\n\n[31 July, 2017] Great progress. Great team and great work",
